{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17611534","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17611534"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T14:11:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T14:11:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16225"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16225","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16225"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.04,0.48,0.39,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8916"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67794"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8916","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8916"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16225"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53259"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"29"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"247"},{"type":"tags","id":"2968"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"8176"},{"type":"tags","id":"10666"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21215"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21218"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22487"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67794","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67794"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents with a three week history of a painful swelling in her right breast. She has not had any previous breast problems, but hurt her breast recently when moving some furniture. On examination there is a 3 cm firm, ill-defined lump in the outer lower quadrant of her right breast. A tissue biopsy is performed. Histological examination reveals necrotic adipose tissue with foamy macrophages, multinucleated giant cells, and chronic inflammatory cells.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Complex sclerosing lesion","Ductal carcinoma in situ","Fat necrosis","Granulomatous mastitis","Intraductal papilloma"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFat necrosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a benign condition that typically occurs following trauma, surgery, or radiation therapy to the breast. The histological findings of foamy macrophages, multinucleated giant cells, and chronic inflammatory cells surrounding necrotic adipose tissue are characteristic features.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other options can be excluded:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplex sclerosing lesion\u003C/strong\u003E shows a mixture of ductal proliferation and stromal fibrosis without significant inflammation or necrosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntraductal papilloma\u003C/strong\u003E is characterized by a fibrovascular core with epithelial proliferation within a duct\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuctal carcinoma in situ\u003C/strong\u003E shows malignant epithelial cells confined within breast ducts\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGranulomatous mastitis\u003C/strong\u003E shows non-caseating granulomas with epithelioid histiocytes but lacks the characteristic fat necrosis\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe history of recent trauma, combined with the characteristic histological findings, strongly supports the diagnosis of fat necrosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fat necrosis of the breast commonly occurs following trauma, surgery, or radiation therapy and presents as a firm mass that can mimic cancer.","Histologically, fat necrosis shows foamy macrophages, multinucleated giant cells, and chronic inflammatory cells surrounding necrotic adipose tissue."],"references":["Kerridge WD, Kryvenko ON, Thompson A, Shah BA. Fat Necrosis of the Breast: A Pictorial Review of the Mammographic, Ultrasound, CT, and MRI Findings with Histopathologic Correlation. Radiol Res Pract. 2015;2015:613139. doi: 10.1155/2015/613139. Epub 2015 Mar 16. PMID: 25861475; PMCID: PMC4378709.","Majithia J, Haria P, Popat P, Katdare A, Chouhan S, Gala KB, Kulkarni S, Thakur M. Fat necrosis: A consultant\u0027s conundrum. Front Oncol. 2023 Feb 16;12:926396. doi: 10.3389/fonc.2022.926396. PMID: 36873302; PMCID: PMC9978799.","Vasei N, Shishegar A, Ghalkhani F, Darvishi M. Fat necrosis in the Breast: A systematic review of clinical. Lipids Health Dis. 2019 Jun 11;18(1):139. doi: 10.1186/s12944-019-1078-4. Erratum in: Lipids Health Dis. 2019 Aug 1;18(1):158. doi: 10.1186/s12944-019-1097-1. PMID: 31185981; PMCID: PMC6560815.","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53259"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16225"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53259","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53259"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-07T09:20:36+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-07T09:21:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8916"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67794"}}},"meta":{"canD